context.rdfs:comment: A web page. Every web page is implicitly assumed to be declared to be of type WebPage, so the various properties about that webpage, such as breadcrumb may be used. We recommend explicit declaration if these properties are specified, but if they are found outside of an itemscope, they will be assumed to be about the page.
context.rdfs:label: WebPage

properties.rdfs:comment: A set of links that can help a user understand and navigate a website hierarchy.
properties.rdfs:label: breadcrumb

properties.rdfs:comment: One of the more significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.
properties.rdfs:label: significantLink

properties.rdfs:comment: A link related to this web page, for example to other related web pages.
properties.rdfs:label: relatedLink

properties.rdfs:comment: Date on which the content on this web page was last reviewed for accuracy and/or completeness.
properties.rdfs:label: lastReviewed

properties.rdfs:comment: Indicates if this web page element is the main subject of the page.
properties.rdfs:label: mainContentOfPage

properties.rdfs:comment: People or organizations that have reviewed the content on this web page for accuracy and/or completeness.
properties.rdfs:label: reviewedBy

properties.rdfs:comment: Indicates the main image on the page.
properties.rdfs:label: primaryImageOfPage

properties.rdfs:comment: The most significant URLs on the page. Typically, these are the non-navigation links that are clicked on the most.
properties.rdfs:label: significantLinks

properties.rdfs:comment: One of the domain specialities to which this web page's content applies.
properties.rdfs:label: specialty
